  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em>A shiv is an improvised weapon intended to replicate a dagger. Whilst shivs are not ideal throwing weapons, they still get the point across.</em></p>\n<p>Deals piercing damage equal to 1d4 + your Strength or Dexterity modifier.</p>\n<p><strong>Finesse. </strong>When making an Attack with a finesse weapon, you use your choice of your Strength or Dexterity modifier for the Attack and Damage Rolls. You must use the same modifier for both rolls.</p>\n<p><strong>Light. </strong>A light weapon is small and easy to handle, making it ideal for use when fighting with two weapons.</p>",
